Row-level security: the one Postgres feature that makes multi-tenancy safe. Per table:

sql
alter table leads enable row level security;

create policy leads_select on leads
  for select using (
    tenant_id = (select tenant_id from users where id = auth.uid())
  );

create policy leads_modify on leads
  for all using (
    tenant_id = (select tenant_id from users where id = auth.uid())
  );
Repeat for every table that has tenant_id. Now even if a frontend bug constructs a query for someone else's tenant, Postgres refuses to return the rows. This is the security boundary, full stop.

